            <title>[LUCENE-1008] document with no term vector fields after documents with term vector fields corrupts the index</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1008</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;If a document with no term-vector-enabled fields is added after&lt;br/&gt;
document(s) that did have term vectors, as part of a single set of&lt;br/&gt;
buffered docs, then the term-vector documents file is corrupted&lt;br/&gt;
because we fail to write a &quot;0&quot; vInt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to Grant for spotting this!&lt;/p&gt;

